==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Workhouse
<hw>Work"house`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Workhouses</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[AS.
<ets>weorch⟦umac⟧s</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A house where any manufacture is carried on; a
workshop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A house in which idle and vicious persons are
confined to labor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A house where the town poor are maintained at public
expense, and provided with labor; a poorhouse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Working</ent>⟦br⟧
